&gt; Some additional information how i got to this question:
&gt;
&gt; I am referring to the JavaDoc and examples concerning the
&gt; org.junit.runners.Parameterized. Within this class the computeParams cast
&gt; the result of the @Parameters method to a List&lt;Object[]&gt;. Therefor i believe
&gt; the JavaDoc should be clearer.
&gt; The computeParams has been defined private, and is therefor no candidate to
&gt; be overriden by a developer to support another Collection implementation. In
&gt; order to support any other Collection implementation you would have to
&gt; override the standard createTest. Plus specify that as the your new class as
&gt; the runner.
&gt;
&gt; It&#39;s just that the JavaDoc for this implementation of Parameterized is not
&gt; accurate, that&#39;s was my problem.
